<div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 shadow-sm p-8 mb-8">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-6">Getting Started</h2>
  
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Find Your Event</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Browse the list of available events on the homepage. Each event will display the event dates, location, venue, and application deadline.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Submit Your Application</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Click "Apply Now" on your desired event and fill out the application form with your personal details, passport information, and travel plans.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. Verify Your Email</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">After submitting, you'll receive a 6-digit verification code via email. Enter this code to confirm your email address.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Wait for Approval</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Your application will be reviewed by the program administrators. You can check your application status at any time using the "Check Application Status" link.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Receive Your Letter</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Once approved, your visa invitation letter will be generated and sent to your email as a PDF attachment.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="bg-white border border-gray-300 shadow-sm p-8 mb-8">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What is a visa invitation letter?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">A visa invitation letter is an official document that supports your visa application by confirming your invitation to attend a specific event. It includes details about the event, your participation, and the organizing organization.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Does a visa invitation letter guarantee visa approval?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">No. A visa invitation letter is one of several supporting documents for your visa application. The final decision rests with the embassy or consulate processing your visa application.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">How long does the approval process take?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Processing times vary depending on the event and volume of applications. We recommend applying as early as possible to allow sufficient time for visa processing.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">What information do I need to apply?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">You'll need your full name (as it appears on your passport), date of birth, nationality, passport number and expiration date, and your planned travel dates.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Can I request changes to my letter?</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700">If you need changes to your visa letter, please contact the program administrators directly using the contact information provided on the event page.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

